    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-10-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="599"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-10-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 589.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s instructions Nos.
                    568 of the 12th and 576 of the 24th ultimo, 581 of the 2d and 583 of the 6th
                    instant, I inclose copies of a letter<note n="1" xml:id="d599fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> from Louis Wertheimer and of two dispatches<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d599fn2">Not printed.</note> from our consul-general at Habana,
                    relating to Mr. Wertheimer’s claim against the Spanish Government based on the
                    action of the Governor-General of Cuba in refusing to allow the shipment of 307
                    bales of tobacco purchased before the date of issue of General Weyler’s
                    proclamation.</p>
                <p>You will present this case with the others to the Spanish Government.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
